verbose_text: The same applied to the nine patients diagnosed with " atypical Usher syndrome " in whom course and/or age of onset of sensorineural hearing impairment and RP did not allow for clear-cut assignment to USH1 or USH2 and who had no additional abnormalities : They were found to have atypical expressions of USH1B (MYO7A), USH1D (CDH23), USH2A, and USH2C (ADGRV1).
evidence: age of onset of sensorineural hearing impairment and RP did not allow for clear-cut assignment to USH1 or USH2
